        <div class="blog-preview">Artificial intelligence is transforming classrooms, but are we ready for the shift? Here's what you need to know...</div>
        <div class="blog-content hidden">
            Artificial intelligence is revolutionizing education, offering tools like personalized learning platforms and AI tutors that adapt to each student's pace and style. While platforms like ChatGPT are helping students grasp difficult concepts, educators worry about over-reliance on technology. AI also raises ethical concerns, such as data privacy and fairness in algorithms. Schools worldwide are experimenting with AI-powered tools to automate administrative tasks, freeing up teachers to focus on instruction. However, experts emphasize the need for teacher training to maximize these benefits while addressing the risks. With AI, education can become more accessible and inclusive, but only if implemented thoughtfully.
