        <h2>Online Learning: The Post-Pandemic Reality</h2>
        <div class="blog-preview">As schools reopen, the future of online education hangs in the balance. Here's what experts predict...</div>
        <div class="blog-content hidden">
            The pandemic forced millions of students online, creating a surge in e-learning platforms like Khan Academy and Coursera. Now, as schools return to in-person learning, hybrid models are emerging as the future. Online tools like Zoom and Google Classroom are becoming permanent fixtures, complementing traditional teaching methods. However, the digital divide remains a challenge, with many students in rural areas still lacking internet access. Policymakers are now focusing on infrastructure improvements to ensure equitable access. Experts agree that online learning isn't a replacement but a powerful supplement to face-to-face education, offering flexibility and new opportunities for growth.
