        <h2>Mental Health in Schools: A Growing Priority</h2>
        <div class="blog-preview">Student mental health is becoming a top priority for educators. Here's how schools are stepping up to support their students...</div>
        <div class="blog-content hidden">
            Mental health awareness in schools has reached a tipping point, with administrators recognizing that academic success and emotional well-being are deeply connected. Programs like mindfulness training, peer counseling, and stress management workshops are being integrated into curricula worldwide. The rise of mental health apps designed for students, such as Calm for Education and Headspace for Schools, provides accessible resources for stress relief and emotional regulation. Schools are also training teachers to recognize signs of mental health struggles and creating safe spaces for students to seek help. However, stigma remains a barrier, and many institutions still lack adequate resources. The goal is clear: create an environment where students can thrive academically and emotionally, preparing them for the challenges of adulthood.
